column8: Ulysses then realized too late he\'d lost Penelope\'s love because he\'d been overly cautious ° T H E ° O N L Y ° W A Y ° T O ° W I N ° her back was to murder the suitors.° ° ° ° ° ° °Collage and quote from Contempt. The collage features images from the film, specifically images of Brigitte Bardot. ° ° ° ° ° ° °Le Mépris (Contempt) is a film about a woman who has grown to despise her husband. Her husband writes screenplays and is working on one for a new film about the Odyssey. The different characters in the film debate their ideas about the Odyssey while paralleling Odysseus and Penelope\'s relationship with the husband and wife. I love the idea that Odysseus didn\'t kill the suitors out of jealous rage after seeing them in his house and knowing they wanted to marry Penelope. He had told Penelope to entertain the suitors so he would not have been surprised to find them in his house. It was when he realized that Penelope despised him that he entered into a fit of rage. Killing the suitors wasn\'t an act of jealousy, it was a desperate attempt to win back Penelope\'s love. She despised his passivity. His apathy repulsed her. Only an uncontrolled and emotional act of violence could win her back. The Odysseus that Penelope loved, would never have let another man enter his house. Odysseus had to kill the man that Penelope despised.

column8: You meet people and they swear they are hard, not emotional, not open. And it\'s true in a sense. This truth has formed itself from their experiences, no denying that. But they may not be aware of their vulnerable; may ignore, may be stubborn, and are surely hurt-- so they are whatever story they tell themselves to cope, whatever has been working or seems like it does. All of that and yet, they still have their water, always did. column8: ⚪ПРО ОЦЕНИВАНИЕ СВОИХ РАБОТ⚪Когда заканчиваю свою работу, я всегда (!) ее анализирую. Как? Сначала смотрю на то, что у меня не получилось, на ошибки , чтобы в следующих работах их не делать. А потом анализирую то, что вышло более удачным. По моему мнению, надо делать и то, и другое, т.к. только хвалить свою работу неправильно, в любом рисунке есть свои минусы, но и видеть только одни минусы тоже нельзя. Всегда надо помнить, что везде есть как плюсы, так и минусы и ни на то, ни на другое не надо закрывать глаза!🌼Законченный портрет прекрасной  @jesssiecaa ❤________________________________When I finish drawing a portrait, I always analyze it.First I look at my mistakes in the drawings.This is important, because there are no drawings in which there would be no cons.And then I look at the advantages in my painting.And this is also important!Since in any drawing there are also advantages💎Portrait of amazing @jesssiecaa ☀️☄enjoy the moments☄

column8: Artemisia Gentileschi fue la primera mujer miembro de la Accademia di Arte del Disegno de Florencia. Muchos la consideran como la "primera pintora mujer", aunque en realidad es la más conocida. Y "conocida" entre comillas (valga la redundancia) ya que tampoco es que sea ¡tan conocida!...Café y nogalina sobre papel....#sketch #drawing #artwork #artoftheday #art #illustration #illustrationart #artstagram #picture #hamdal #paint #portrait #sketchbook #caffè #coffee #ArtemisiaGentileschi #painter #woman
